					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="1361261"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1396039853 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">28 Mar 2014 20:50</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2000684">
									

<p>There's elements to this that don't agree with me. It feels a little overwrought emotionally, with the whole &quot;I don't know whether I want to live or not&quot; thing, and there's some odd turns of phrase here and there (&quot;panic spread like fire on match&quot;, huh?).</p>
<p>However, this is a cohesive tale with an actual story behind it, which gets into enough detail to do a little development of the characters participating in the action. It adds something to the skips it's using as source material, which to me fulfills the spirit of this contest in highlighting lesser-known works.</p>
<p>I feel generally unmoved, to be honest, but on principle and technical merit I'll upvote this one.</p>

							</div>

								
					
